The paper presents a machine learning method for predicting molecular properties, specifically the atomization energy of molecules. This falls under the category of computational chemistry and materials science, which is closely related to machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also discusses the use of graph kernels, which are commonly used in computer vision and natural language processing, suggesting a possible connection to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper uses an active learning procedure, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and computational engineering (cs.CE).
